# Restore Point

This project has a **restore point** (latest baseline). Any previous restore point is superseded; this is the only active one. All future work starts from this state.

When the user says any of the following:

- "move to restore point"
- "restore point"
- "go to restore point"
- "revert to restore point"

**You must restore the codebase to the saved state:**

1. Read `.cursor/restore-point/RESTORE_POINT.md` for the list of snapshot files and their target paths.
2. Copy each file from `.cursor/restore-point/` to its target path, overwriting the current file.
3. Treat the restore point as the source of truth; any changes made after the restore point are removed by this restore.

Example: if the doc says `TemplateEditor.jsx` → `frontend/src/pages/TemplateEditor.jsx`, copy `.cursor/restore-point/TemplateEditor.jsx` to `frontend/src/pages/TemplateEditor.jsx`.
